pythia}$,\nwhere one can conveniently control MPIs by the program parameters, and HEF for\na few unintegrated gluon distributions (UGDs). We find that the energy\ndependence of $b$ is very sensitive to the particular choice of UGD and in some\nmodels it resembles predictions of the Monte Carlo models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 1 Aug 2016 18:54:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-03-22"}
